# Power BI Embedded — Environment Variables
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Copy this file to .env and fill in ONE of the options below.
#
# ── OPTION A: Publish to web (easiest — report is publicly visible) ──────────
#
#  1. Open Tsunami_dash.pbix in Power BI Desktop
#  2. File → Publish → Publish to Power BI  (sign in with a free account)
#  3. Open app.powerbi.com and navigate to your published report
#  4. File → Embed report → Publish to web (public)
#  5. Copy the  src="..."  URL from the generated <iframe> tag and paste below
#
VITE_POWERBI_IFRAME_URL=

# ── OPTION B: Secure embed via SDK (requires Azure AD app registration) ───────
#
#  1. Open Tsunami_dash.pbix in Power BI Desktop
#  2. Publish the report to Power BI Service (app.powerbi.com)
#  3. In the service, open the published report
#  4. Click  File → Embed report → Developer Playground  to get the Embed URL
#     and Report ID
#  5. Register an Azure AD application with the Power BI API permission
#     "Report.ReadAll" and generate an embed token using the REST API:
#     POST https://api.powerbi.com/v1.0/myorg/reports/{reportId}/GenerateToken
#  6. Paste the values below
#
# Reference: https://docs.microsoft.com/power-bi/developer/embedded/embed-sample-for-customers
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

VITE_POWERBI_EMBED_URL=
VITE_POWERBI_ACCESS_TOKEN=
VITE_POWERBI_REPORT_ID=
